      <div class="msgContentFrame">I've been receiving main hand weapon skill from blocks since open beta.  Doesn't matter what class I'm on: GLA, THM, or CON...if you've got a shield equip and you block you can get skill for your main hand weapon out of it.  I think it's intended as a balancing mechanic given that a lot of abilities a gladiator might use while tanking would not necessarily ear them skillups (ie. Rampart, Defender, Guard uses stamina/time but doesn't explicitly grant skill points on its own, etc.)  Also, it helps to keep your shield skill from eating all of your GLA skillups when tanking fast hitting mobs or groups.  Gladiators are already complaining that they use too much stamina on abilities that can't grant SP, so if you're tanking and taking hits, the sword skill points you get from blocking help make up for that a bit.</div>
      <div class="msgFtFrame">
